p: Other chemotypes present in literature are characterized by methyleugenol (62.0%), recognized in the specimens collected from Pará State (Brazil) and Chocò (Colombia); by 1,8-cineole (61.8%) and sabinene (16.4%), identified in two specimens collected in Piauí State (Brazil); and by β-caryophyllene (78.6%) and 1,8-cineole (13.0%), which are the main compounds of the Maranhão (Brazil) and Germany O. campechianum EO [ 15, 16, 17, 22].
